I"1<p>If a pair consisting of a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-memory">dynamical system</a> and a certain <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/ds-can-be-entrained-by-input">input</a> has the echo state property, then regardless of the initial <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-a-certain-anatomy">state</a> of the DS, the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/metabolism-influences-neural-dynamics">dynamics</a> will converge to a unifying pattern following a transient washout.</p>
